node.text: It’s good our country is finally out of #Afghanistan but the way it was handled was horrible and embarrassing. I don’t put any of that blame on our military — they are the best in the world. I do place a lot of blame on #JoeBiden. He made this into a crisis with his negligence and sloppiness and it didn’t have to be that way.  13 service members did not need to lose their lives. Even Democrats probably know that #PresidentTrump would have handled it better. Much better. It’s also pretty lame that the #Taliban inherited so much of our weapons and equipment — that right there tells you this whole thing was very ill-planned.

node.title: U.S. General Announces Completion of Withdrawal from Afghanistan

node.text: I want to express my most heartfelt wishes, thoughts and prayers to the families of these brave soldiers who lost their life in #Kabul #Afghanistan a few days ago. Several of them were from my state of California. What makes these deaths difficult for me (and probably you) is that it could have all been avoided if we had real leaders in charge who knew what they were doing. But we don’t have that — we have #JoeBiden and #KamalaHarris. Heartbreaking. #FoxNews

node.title: 13 Brave Heroes Who Lost Their Lives Saving Others in Afghanistan

It’s quite telling when even #CNN turns on #JoeBiden and calls him a foreign policy failure. All you had to do was look at his past.  #JakeTapper: We are “watching a tragic foreign policy disaster unfold before our eyes...The rapid crumbling of #Afghanistan has caught the #Biden #WhiteHouse flat footed.”

“It seems shocking that President Biden could’ve been so wrong” 

#SleepyJoe #KamalaHarris #Comeonman

node.text: Buildings can be rebuilt but lives can not be replaced. I remember that early morning 20 years ago today very well. I had just gotten back from Washington DC two weeks before #911 happened. My gf (at the time) and I were visiting her family on the east coast and it was my first time in DC. I was sleeping at her house when I got a frantic call from my mom saying we were at war. I turned the tv on to a horrifying sight as the first tower was burning. A few minutes later I watched live as the second plane hit the second tower. I was in shock because I had never seen anything like that and I never even imagined a #terroristattack on that scale, up until then. What was especially difficult for me was imagining all those poor souls trapped up in those towers with no way out, except to jump. And I think about all the #firefighters and #firstresponders who were in those towers trying to rescue people. Take a moment of silence and remember all those who lost their lives on those planes, in #NewYork, at the #Pentagon, and on that field in #Shanksville #pennsylvania. I will #neverforget and I will  #alwaysremember.  I also want to acknowledge the heart-breaking sacrifice of so many in the #NYFD who died years later from cancer related to being at the #groundzero site with the overwhelmingly difficult task of recovering bodies and cleaning up the debris. All of those people were heroes and all of them will forever be remembered that way. 🙏🏼 #20thanniversary

node.text:
"Why force a rape or incest victim to carry a pregnancy to term?"

#Texas #Governor #GregAbbott.: "It doesn't require that at all. It provides six weeks for a person to be able to get an abortion.” Good question and good answer. This seems like a good middle ground between those who want to ban abortion completely without exception and those who think it’s okay to do it during the 2nd and 3rd trimesters.  You can’t criminalize abortion completely because people will still do it anyway, just in less safe and sanitary ways. But you can definitely use a firm cut off point so that if someone wants to do it, they do it ASAP. I’ve always believed in a woman’s right to choose but you have to come up with a cut off point, and you can’t just be flippant about it. 6 weeks sounds reasonable. Do it before then or carry to term and then maybe allow another family who wants a kid to adopt them. I know many will argue that life begins at conception and they’re probably right. But I think you have to make common sense exceptions, especially when it comes to rape or incest. But having consensual unprotected sex and then using abortion as a means of birth control is extremely irresponsible.

node.text: It’s good our country is finally out of #Afghanistan but the way it was handled was horrible and embarrassing. I don’t put any of that blame on our military — they are the best in the world. I do place a lot of blame on #JoeBiden. He made this into a crisis with his negligence and sloppiness and it didn’t have to be that way.  13 service members did not need to lose their lives. Even Democrats probably know that #PresidentTrump would have handled it better. Much better. It’s also pretty lame that the #Taliban inherited so much of our weapons and equipment — that right there tells you this whole thing was very ill-planned.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by 𝕌𝕟𝕗𝕚𝕝𝕥𝕖𝕣𝕖𝕕.ℙ𝕠𝕝𝕚𝕥𝕚𝕔𝕤 on August 30, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Tibbetts, 20, was remembered as a kind and bright young woman who was quick to help others and planned a career in child psychology. Her mother, Laura Calderwood, addressed Bahena Rivera in a victim impact statement read by a representative to the court.'.

Photo by 𝕌𝕟𝕗𝕚𝕝𝕥𝕖𝕣𝕖𝕕.ℙ𝕠𝕝𝕚𝕥𝕚𝕔𝕤 on August 30, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Calderwood recalled being told by tearful investigators that her daughter's body had been found, and racing to inform relatives of the heartbreaking news before they learned what happened from the media. The hardest conversation was with Mollie's grandmother, who was in disbelief that someone "could harm such a beautiful, vibrant young woman so full of promise," she said.'.

Photo by 𝕌𝕟𝕗𝕚𝕝𝕥𝕖𝕣𝕖𝕕.ℙ𝕠𝕝𝕚𝕥𝕚𝕔𝕤 on August 30, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Calderwood recalled being told by tearful investigators that her daughter's body had been found, and racing to inform relatives of the heartbreaking news before they learned what happened from the media. The hardest conversation was with Mollie's grandmother, who was in disbelief that someone "could harm suc such a beautiful, vibrant young woman so full of promise," she said.'.

Photo by 𝕌𝕟𝕗𝕚𝕝𝕥𝕖𝕣𝕖𝕕.ℙ𝕠𝕝𝕚𝕥𝕚𝕔𝕤 on August 30, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Tibbetts vanished on a rural road outside her hometown of Brooklyn, lowa, population 1,700, while while out for one of her near-daily runs on July 18, 2018. Bahena Rivera led investigators to her body a month later. Family members and co-workers feared something was wrong when Tibbetts did not show up for her summer job at a daycare the next morning.'.

Photo by 𝕌𝕟𝕗𝕚𝕝𝕥𝕖𝕣𝕖𝕕.ℙ𝕠𝕝𝕚𝕥𝕚𝕔𝕤 on August 30, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Hundreds of volunteers and law enforcement officers searched for her for weeks but came up empty. Investigators began focusing on Bahena Rivera, who worked under an alias at a nearby dairy farm, after finding a homeowner's surveillance video appearing to show his Chevy Malibu repeatedly driving past Tibbetts while she ran.'.

Photo by 𝕌𝕟𝕗𝕚𝕝𝕥𝕖𝕣𝕖𝕕.ℙ𝕠𝕝𝕚𝕥𝕚𝕔𝕤 on August 30, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'After a lengthy interrogation, Bahena Rivera led authorities to a field where he had buried Tibbetts' body under leaves and stalks. Only her bright running shoes were visible. An autopsy found she had been stabbed several times.'.

Photo by 𝕌𝕟𝕗𝕚𝕝𝕥𝕖𝕣𝕖𝕕.ℙ𝕠𝕝𝕚𝕥𝕚𝕔𝕤 on August 30, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Bahena Rivera told investigators that he approached Tibbetts because he found her attractive, and that he fought with her after she threatened to call the police. He said he then blacked out and came to as he was driving with her body in his trunk.'.
Photo by 𝕌𝕟𝕗𝕚𝕝𝕥𝕖𝕣𝕖𝕕.ℙ𝕠𝕝𝕚𝕥𝕚𝕔𝕤 on August 30, 2021. May be a closeup of 1 person and outdoors.

node.text: A very confused #JoeBiden: "I'm here, uh, uh, eh, the #FEMA's director's on, uh, uh, FEMA Director Criswell, she's on. And I'm here with, uh, with my senior adviser and a boy who knows #Louisiana very, very well, man, and, and #NewOrleans, Cedric Richmond." 👏🏼 Boy that was tough getting through all those words and names, tell you what. Is it nap time yet, Jack? #comeonman I don’t think he’ll ever know his #FemaDirector’s name. It’s #DeanneCriswell. Remember Joe?  You appointed her?  No?  And all this despite him wearing an ear piece with his aides guiding him through every single word and name. Imagine #SleepyJoe completely on his own. 👀 #hurricaneida
